meta-licheepizero-voicecommand
==============================

meta-licheepizero-voicecommand is a Yocto meta-layer for the LicheePi Zero Dock board.
It provides voice command processing, SQL database connectivity, and Qt application support.

Dependencies
============

  URI: https://git.yoctoproject.org/poky
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: https://github.com/openembedded/meta-openembedded
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: https://github.com/meta-qt5/meta-qt5
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: https://github.com/lichee-pi/meta-licheepizero
  branch: kirkstone


Layer Contents
==============

recipes-apps/voicecommand/    C++ voice command application with MFCC-based WAV analysis
recipes-apps/sqlclient/       FreeTDS SQL Server client application
recipes-myqtapp/myqtapp/      Qt5 application with SQL/ODBC database connectivity
recipes-kernel/linux/         Kernel DTS patches for microphone and UART2 enablement
recipes-core/init-ifupdown/   Network interfaces configuration (static IP + DHCP)
recipes-database/freetds/     FreeTDS 1.3.10 database library recipe
recipes-example/example/      Bitbake example recipe


Adding the meta-licheepizero-voicecommand layer to your build
==============================================================

Run the following command:

  bitbake-layers add-layer meta-licheepizero-voicecommand


